  "text": "Examples Where Assumption 2 Is verified: In Proposition 3 below, the Markov property of the process (F n , G n ) n∈Z is obvious, while in Proposition 4, it can be easily checked from Equation [CITATION_1] . Moreover, in both propositions, it is well known that the Markov process (F n , G n ) n∈Z is an ergodic process satisfying Assumptions 2-(a) and 2-(b) [CITATION_2] . We shall focus on Assumptions 2-(c) and 2-(d).",
